title.narrative: CONCERT (Communicating, Networking, and Capacity-Building To Effectively Respond Together)

description.narrative: CONCERT aims to reduce fertility and population growth; lower the risk of HIV/AIDS; and reduce maternal and infant and under-five mortality rates. The project has broad national coverage through mass media, campaigns, and capacity building, as well as intensive implementation through projects local partners. During the life of the project, CONCERT will: 1) Work to improve coordination and planning by developing a platform for health messaging and integrated communication strategies. 2) Develop a multi-media campaign using a centrepiece radio programme and family health booklet. 3) Develop a community mobilization toolkit. 4) Support capacity development of the HEU and explore the creation of an S/BCC knowledge management system. 5) Develop and document best practices, introducing new approaches to S/BCC and conduct operations research.
